1800.value:
Weekly Life-Changing Ticket Reward
Overview: 
Players who fail in the game will receive a "Life-Changing Ticket," serving as proof of participation in the weekly failure prize pool Reward.
Each Life-Changing Ticket has a unique serial number, and players can hold multiple vouchers to increase their chances of winning.
80% of the weekly prize pool will be distributed as rewards, while 20% will roll over to the next week's prize pool.

Example:
1. Prize Pool and Number of Winners:
   Total Prize Pool: 100,000 MNT.
   Total Life-Changing Tickets Issued: 80,000.
   Total Winners for the Week: 10 fixed winners + 300 dynamic winners (adjusted based on the prize pool size).

2. Reward Allocation:
   80% of the weekly prize pool (80,000 MNT) is divided into two parts:
   ¬∑50% (40,000 MNT): Allocated to the top 10 winners.
   ¬∑50% (40,000 MNT): Evenly distributed among the remaining 300 winners.

Reward Breakdown:
1. Top 10 Winners (50% of the prize pool, 40,000 MNT):
   1st Place: 20% of 80,000 MNT = 16,000 MNT.
   2nd Place: 8% of 80,000 MNT = 6,400 MNT.
   3rd Place: 4% of 80,000 MNT = 3,200 MNT.
   4th Place: 3% of 80,000 MNT = 2,400 MNT.
   5th to 10th Places: 2.5% of 80,000 MNT each = 2,000 MNT per person (12,000 MNT total).
2. Remaining 300 Winners (50% of the prize pool, 40,000 MNT):
   The remaining 300 winners will share the leftover prize pool equally:
   40,000 √∑ 300 ‚âà 133.63 MNT per person.

Reward Rules:
. Winning Chances: Each Life-Changing Ticket has an independent chance of winning.
2. Reward Distribution:
   First, the top 10 winners are drawn and rewards are allocated according to the rules.
   The remaining prize pool is evenly distributed among other winners.
3. Transparency: Reward results will be recorded on-chain to ensure fairness and transparency.
